And that's what I've been comparing it to... it's obviously not as good, but it's also 1 mana and 10 cents, as opposed to 3 and 50 bucks.

I'm not saying it's the second coming, I'm just saying it _should_ see play in a lot of decks.

Of course I toned down your praise of that card in the review! You likened it to Teferi’s Protection! I didn’t want you to get shat on. 

Gideon’s Sacrifice is a Holy Day that requires you to have a creature in play. Teferi’s Protection saves you from combat, combos, board wipes, and everything else. Regardless of the cost of the cards, the comparison is off-base.

Still disagree there. The comparison with holy day/fog is off base, because those aren't one sided and can't create advantage in the same way that Boros Charm or Heroic Intervention type effects can. 

As for directly comparing to protection, sure it's worse. That doesn't mean it's not comparable as an additional or budget option.
Call me delusional,  but I really do believe it'll be the best monowhite card of the set.
Or at least most played.
